<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="div" id="div">div</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Sintaxe:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdlib&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">div_t</span> <span class="kw3">div</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> numerator, <span class="kw4">int</span> denominator <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

A função div() devolve o quociente e resto da operação numerador / denominador.
A estrutura div_t está definida em cstdlib, e tem pelo menos:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     <span class="kw4">int</span> quot<span class="sy4">;</span>   <span class="co1">// O quociente</span>
     <span class="kw4">int</span> rem<span class="sy4">;</span>    <span class="co1">// O resto</span></pre>
<p>

Por exemplo, o código seguinte mostra o quociente e resto de x/y:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     <span class="kw4">div_t</span> temp<span class="sy4">;</span>
     temp <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="kw3">div</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> x, y <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
     <span class="kw3">printf</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;%d divided by %d yields %d with a remainder of %d<span class="es1">\n</span>&quot;</span>,
             x, y, temp.<span class="me1">quot</span>, temp.<span class="me1">rem</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
O C++ também fornece as seguintes formas sobre-carregadas (overload):

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdlib&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">ldiv_t</span> <span class="kw3">div</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> numerator, <span class="kw4">long</span> denominator <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a ldiv()</span></pre>
<p>
Tópicos Relacionados: <a href="ldiv" class="wikilink1" title="br-pt:numeric:c:ldiv">ldiv</a>

</p>

</div>
